---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  pageType="other"
  title="Privacy &mdash; Kunal"
  description="What this site collects, why, and how to control it."
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>

  <p>
    This is a personal blog. I want it to be as boring as possible from a privacy
    standpoint. Here's exactly what happens when you visit.
  </p>

  <h2>What gets collected</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> records anonymous traffic data:
      page views, language, content group, scroll depth (25/50/75/100%), and
      outbound link clicks. IP addresses are anonymised by GA4 by default.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Giscus</strong> (the comments box) is loaded from giscus.app and
      hands off to GitHub if you choose to comment. Loading it sets cookies
      from those domains. If you never interact, no comment data is collected.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Lyket</strong> (the reactions widget) records anonymous like
      counts per post.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Fonts</strong> are loaded from Google Fonts, which logs requests
      as part of normal CDN operation.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What does NOT get collected</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No advertising cookies. No remarketing. No ad personalisation.</li>
    <li>No selling or sharing of personal data.</li>
    <li>No newsletters, no email capture, no behavioural profiling.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your controls</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      The cookie banner lets you <strong>Decline</strong> analytics cookies.
      If you do, GA4 runs in cookieless mode and most signals are dropped.
    </li>
    <li>
      If your browser sends <em>Do Not Track</em>, the analytics script is not
      loaded at all.
    </li>
    <li>
      Clear site data in your browser to revoke any choice and see the banner
      again.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal basis</h2>
  <p>
    Analytics consent is requested under GDPR / ePrivacy. Where required,
    Consent Mode v2 keeps analytics storage denied by default until you accept.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions or removal requests: open an issue on
    <a href="https://github.com/findkunal/personal-site">the site's GitHub repo</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
